    Start([Complete Logic Study Journey]) --> ChoosePath{Choose Your Approach}

    ChoosePath --> FoundationalPath["Foundational Path<br/>Canonical Works & Historical Development"]
    ChoosePath --> PracticalPath["Practical Path<br/>Textbooks & Study Resources"]

    %% Foundational Path
    FoundationalPath --> FoundationCanon{Foundation Level - Canon}
    FoundationCanon --> BasicConcepts["Basic Concepts - Canon<br/>Copi & Cohen: Introduction to Logic<br/>Hurley: Concise Introduction to Logic<br/>Beall: Logic - The Basics"]
    FoundationCanon --> HistoricalContext["Historical Context - Canon<br/>Kneale & Kneale: Development of Logic<br/>Jorgensen: History of Western Logic<br/>Bobzien: Ancient Logic"]

    BasicConcepts --> PropositionalCanon["Propositional Logic - Canon<br/>Goldrei: Propositional & Predicate Calculus<br/>Kleene: Mathematical Logic<br/>Grassmann: Logic & Discrete Mathematics"]
    HistoricalContext --> AncientCanon["Ancient Logic - Canon<br/>Aristotle: Organon (Complete Works)<br/>Corcoran: Ancient Logic & Modern Interpretations<br/>Sandbach: The Stoics"]

    %% Practical Path
    PracticalPath --> FoundationPractical{Foundation Level - Study}
    FoundationPractical --> BasicTexts["Basic Logic Textbooks<br/>Bergmann, Moor & Nelson: The Logic Book<br/>Shoenfield: Mathematical Logic<br/>van Dalen: Logic and Structure<br/>Lemmon: Beginning Logic"]
    FoundationPractical --> IntroBooks["Introductory Resources<br/>Tomassi: Logic<br/>Smith: An Introduction to Formal Logic<br/>Forbes: Modern Logic<br/>Volpano: Introduction to Mathematical Logic"]

    %% Convergence Point
    PropositionalCanon --> IntermediateLevel{Intermediate Level}
    AncientCanon --> IntermediateLevel
    BasicTexts --> IntermediateLevel
    IntroBooks --> IntermediateLevel

    %% Intermediate Level - Combined Resources
    IntermediateLevel --> ModernLogic["Modern Logic Revolution<br/>CANON: Frege: Begriffsschrift<br/>CANON: Russell & Whitehead: Principia Mathematica<br/>STUDY: Dummett: Frege - Philosophy of Language<br/>STUDY: Grattan-Guinness: Search for Mathematical Roots"]

    IntermediateLevel --> SetTheory["Set Theory & Foundations<br/>CANON: Kunen: Set Theory - Independence Proofs<br/>CANON: Halmos: Naive Set Theory<br/>STUDY: Devlin: The Joy of Sets<br/>STUDY: Jech: Set Theory (3rd edition)"]

    IntermediateLevel --> ProofTheory["Proof Theory<br/>CANON: Takeuti: Proof Theory<br/>CANON: Gentzen: Collected Papers<br/>STUDY: Troelstra & Schwichtenberg: Basic Proof Theory<br/>STUDY: Girard: Proofs and Types"]

    ModernLogic --> MathematicalLogic["Mathematical Logic<br/>CANON: Bell & Machover: Course in Mathematical Logic<br/>CANON: Boolos, Burgess & Jeffrey: Computability and Logic<br/>STUDY: Chang & Keisler: Model Theory<br/>STUDY: Marker: Model Theory - An Introduction"]

    SetTheory --> MathematicalLogic
    ProofTheory --> MathematicalLogic

    MathematicalLogic --> AdvancedLevel{Advanced Level}

    %% Advanced Level - Combined Resources
    AdvancedLevel --> ModalLogic["Modal Logic<br/>CANON: Chellas: Modal Logic - An Introduction<br/>CANON: Lewis: Counterfactuals<br/>STUDY: Hughes & Cresswell: A New Introduction to Modal Logic<br/>STUDY: Goldblatt: Logics of Time and Computation"]

    AdvancedLevel --> NonClassicalLogic["Non-Classical Logics<br/>CANON: Priest: Introduction to Non-Classical Logic<br/>CANON: Troelstra & van Dalen: Constructivism in Mathematics<br/>STUDY: Restall: Introduction to Substructural Logics<br/>STUDY: Dunn & Hardegree: Algebraic Methods"]

    AdvancedLevel --> PhilosophicalLogic["Philosophical Logic<br/>CANON: Burgess: Philosophical Logic - An Introduction<br/>CANON: Sainsbury: Paradoxes<br/>STUDY: Read: Thinking About Logic<br/>STUDY: Gamut: Logic, Language and Meaning"]

    ModalLogic --> SpecializedLevel{Specialized Level}
    NonClassicalLogic --> SpecializedLevel
    PhilosophicalLogic --> SpecializedLevel

    %% Specialized Level - Combined Resources
    SpecializedLevel --> ComputationalLogic["Computational Logic<br/>CANON: Lloyd: Logic Programming<br/>CANON: Handbook of Automated Reasoning<br/>STUDY: Sterling & Shapiro: The Art of Prolog<br/>STUDY: Fitting: First-Order Logic and Automated Theorem Proving"]

    SpecializedLevel --> CategoryTheory["Category Theory<br/>CANON: Mac Lane: Category Theory for Working Mathematician<br/>CANON: Lawvere & Schanuel: Conceptual Mathematics<br/>STUDY: Pierce: Basic Category Theory for Computer Scientists<br/>STUDY: Goldblatt: Topoi: The Categorial Analysis of Logic"]

    SpecializedLevel --> LogicApplications["Logic Applications<br/>CANON: Huth & Ryan: Logic in Computer Science<br/>CANON: Stenning & van Lambalgen: Human Reasoning<br/>STUDY: Russell & Norvig: Artificial Intelligence (Logic sections)<br/>STUDY: Blackburn & Bos: Representation and Inference"]

    ComputationalLogic --> ContemporaryLevel{Contemporary Level}
    CategoryTheory --> ContemporaryLevel
    LogicApplications --> ContemporaryLevel

    %% Contemporary Level
    ContemporaryLevel --> QuantumLogic["Quantum Logic<br/>CANON: Beltrametti & Cassinelli: Quantum Logic<br/>STUDY: Nielsen & Chuang: Quantum Computation and Information"]

    ContemporaryLevel --> CuttingEdge["Cutting-Edge Research<br/>CANON: Simpson: Subsystems of Second Order Arithmetic<br/>CANON: Univalent Foundations Program: HoTT Book<br/>STUDY: Kohlenbach: Applied Proof Theory<br/>STUDY: Research Journals & Conference Proceedings"]

    %% Practical Resources Branch
    ContemporaryLevel --> PracticalResources["Practical Study Resources<br/>SOFTWARE: Lean Theorem Prover, Coq, Isabelle/HOL<br/>ONLINE: MIT OpenCourseWare, Stanford Logic courses<br/>EXERCISES: Bergmann: The Logic Book exercises<br/>COMMUNITIES: Logic study groups and forums"]

    %% Alternative Entry Points
    Start --> AlternativeEntry["Alternative Entry Points by Background"]
    AlternativeEntry --> MathBackground["Mathematics Background<br/>START: Set Theory canonical texts<br/>SUPPLEMENT: Mathematical logic textbooks"]
    AlternativeEntry --> PhilosophyBackground["Philosophy Background<br/>START: Ancient Logic canonical works<br/>SUPPLEMENT: Philosophical logic textbooks"]
    AlternativeEntry --> CSBackground["Computer Science Background<br/>START: Computational logic resources<br/>SUPPLEMENT: Logic programming texts"]

    MathBackground --> SetTheory
    PhilosophyBackground --> AncientCanon
    CSBackground --> ComputationalLogic

    %% Cross-connections showing relationships
    QuantumLogic -.-> MathematicalLogic
    CuttingEdge -.-> CategoryTheory
    PracticalResources -.-> ComputationalLogic

